.TH simple_shell "NOVEMBER, 7th 2022" "1" "simple shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell

The simple shell loosly recreates the original shell, written by Ken Thompson
.SH SYNOPSIS

.B $ ./hsh
.PP
.BR $
.PP
.BR $ ls /
.PP
.B bin  dev  home  initrd.img.old  lib64   media  opt   root  sbin  sys  usr  var  vmlinuz.old
.PP
.B boot  etc  initrd.img  lib   lost+found  mnt  proc  run   srv   tmp  vagrant  vmlinuz

.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs commands in both interactive and non-interactive modes. Resolves PATH to commands.

.B Return Value
.RS 3
Returns exit codes / error codes (if any)
.RE

.SH NOTES
The program doesn't account for flags, fields, precision, or length modifiers.

.SH EXAMPLE
.RS 3 $ ./hsh
.PP
.BR $
.PP
.BR $ ls /
.PP
.B bin  dev  home  initrd.img.old  lib64   media  opt   root  sbin  sys  usr  var  vmlinuz.old
.PP
.B boot  etc  initrd.img  lib   lost+found  mnt  proc  run   srv   tmp  vagrant  vmlinuz
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.B sh
